The paper deals with coding theory and its application to lattice schemes, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses the Singleton bound, which is a fundamental concept in coding theory and is relevant to the sub-categories of coding and cryptography (cs.CC), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also presents new upper bounds on code size, which is relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) where network coding is used to optimize data transmission.
